<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="uk">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>Document</title>
    <style>
        body { font-family: sans-serif; max-width: 800px; margin: 20px auto; padding: 10px; }
        .article { border-bottom: 2px solid #ccc; padding-bottom: 15px; }
        .comment-box { border-bottom: 1px solid #ddd; padding: 10px 0; }
        .comment-name { font-weight: bold; }
        .comment-date { color: gray; font-size: 12px; }
        form { margin-top: 20px; background: #f9f9f9; padding: 15px; border-radius: 5px; }
        input, textarea { width: 100%; margin-bottom: 10px; display: block; padding: 5px; }
        button { padding: 8px 15px; cursor: pointer; }
    </style>
</head>
<body>

    <div class="article">
        <h2>What is Lorem Ipsum?</h2>
        <p>Lorem Ipsum is simply dummy text of the printing and typesetting industry. Lorem Ipsum has been the industry's standard dummy text ever since the 1500s...</p>
    </div>

    <h3>Коментарі:</h3>
    <div id="commentsList">
        <div class="comment-box">
            <span class="comment-name">Antoine</span> <span class="comment-date">22.03.2018</span>
            <p>Best comment from Antoine!</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <form id="commentForm">
        <h4>Leave a comment</h4>
        <label>Name:</label>
        <input type="text" id="userName" required>
        
        <label>Comment:</label>
        <textarea id="userText" rows="4" required></textarea>
        
        <button type="submit">Add comment</button>
    </form>

    <script>
        let form = document.getElementById('commentForm');
        let commentsList = document.getElementById('commentsList');

        form.addEventListener('submit', function(e) {
            e.preventDefault();

            let name = document.getElementById('userName').value;
            let text = document.getElementById('userText').value;
            

            let now = new Date();
            let dateStr = now.getDate() + "." + (now.getMonth() + 1) + "." + now.getFullYear();

            let newComment = document.createElement('div');
            newComment.className = 'comment-box';
            newComment.innerHTML = `
                <span class="comment-name">${name}</span> <span class="comment-date">${dateStr}</span>
                <p>${text}</p>
            `;

            commentsList.appendChild(newComment);
            form.reset();
        });
    </script>
</body>
</html>
